Ghana will host the first leg of their 2022 FIFA World Cup playoff against Nigeria. The match will be played at the Babayara Stadium in Kumasi. Over the two legs, only one of the West African rivals will get the chance to clinch one of the five spots available for the continent at the tournament later this year. Both teams reached the playoffs after topping their respective groups in the third round of the World Cup qualification, each with 13 points from six matches. Kick off will be 8.30pm Nigerian time. Nigeria XI vs Ghana: Uzoho; Aina, Balogun, Troost-Ekong, Sanusi; Aribo, Iheanacho, Bonke; Simon, Osimhen, Chukwueze. Friday, March 25
First half: Both sides have chances, but no goals in the opening 45 minutes. Half time. Second half: No goals in the final 45 minutes of the game. Full time: Nigeria have been held to a 0-0 draw by Ghana in Kumasi.